1. Registration to be done first.

 2. There will be short audition thing to shortlist the participants. (Round 1)

 3. Now, teams of 3 participants in each will be made. Using the talent they have to impress the audience there and collect the amount.

 4. They need to get the audience attracted towards them. One coordinator will be given to each team.

 5. After the time is over, they need to report to the coordinators for evaluation.

 1. Each team can have maximum 2 member

 2. Platform -C/C++

 3. Teams will be judged on their accuracy as well as their efficiency.

Talent is not all about juggling balls or eating fire. For me, talent is simply doing the best with what we have. Kindness could be a talent. So could be survival. It is easy to think that talent leading to riches is the end goal. But using your talents need not be a competitive catapult - it can be a little joy for a full weekend. Or a stress buster on a busy day. It is the mere act of pursuing something to the best of your ability every day that makes you unique. The event is all about playing a 1 vs 1 quiz on a mobile app “QuizUp”. The quiz consists of seven questions related to a selected topic and 10 seconds is allotted for answering each question. The quick correct response will get higher points in comparison to a slower response and no points for a wrong answer. At the end of the game the score of each player will be displayed on the screen according to which a winner will be declared.
